docs.lead_paragraph: MONTEVIDEO, Nov. 5 -- It appeared this afternoon that the only accomplishment of the tri-partite meat trade conference among Argentina, Brazil and Uruguay would be an agreement designed to break up the packers' conference thereby they fix the proportion of exports each packer may ship to Great Britain.

docs.snippet: BUENOS AIRES, Nov. 6. -- All grains weakened last week from the previous week's low levels. Prices rallied slightly on Saturday, but closed lower than on the previous Saturday. Wheat was hardest hit and declined from 6.25 pesos a quintal to 5.85...
docs.lead_paragraph: BUENOS AIRES, Nov. 6. -- All grains weakened last week from the previous week's low levels. Prices rallied slightly on Saturday, but closed lower than on the previous Saturday. Wheat was hardest hit and declined from 6.25 pesos a quintal to 5.85 pesos, equivalent to from 43 to 41 cents a bushel.
